# Batch trade template (CSV). Drop a copy of this file (renamed without ".sample")
# into data/trades/ and the pricer will load every row as a trade.
#
# NOTE: comment lines below contain NO commas on purpose so this file opens
# as a clean table in Excel. The real header row is the line just above
# the SWAP_TEST rows; comment lines sit in column A.
#
# Every CONVENTION is per-leg (Bloomberg vocabulary). Only economic terms are
# shared. Column order does not matter (matched by name); an omitted column
# behaves exactly like a blank cell -> the default below applies.
#
# === SECTION 1: PRICING INPUTS (used by the pricer) ===
#
# Columns:
#   --- Required (economic terms; must be present; no default) ---
#   trade_id                  unique label e.g. SWAP_TEST_001 (AMEX scheme: trailing id only)
#   notional                  positive number e.g. 500000000
#   pay_fixed                 true = pay fixed/receive float | false = receive fixed/pay float
#   fixed_rate                decimal e.g. 0.0541 = 5.41%
#   start_date                ISO date | effective / first accrual day
#   maturity_date             ISO date | termination / last accrual end (must be > start_date)
#   fixed_frequency           1Y / 6M / 3M / 1M / 1W / 1D
#   fixed_daycount            ACT/360 | ACT/365F | 30/360 | 30E/360 | ACT/ACT-ISDA
#
#   --- Fixed leg conventions (optional) ---
#   fixed_bus_day_adj         "Bus Day Adj": roll for accrual-end dates; <roll>; blank => ModifiedFollowing
#   fixed_eff_date_adj        "Eff Date Adj": roll for the effective date; <roll>; blank => fixed_bus_day_adj
#   fixed_pay_date_adj        "Pay Date Adj" (BBG-derived); <roll>; blank => fixed_bus_day_adj
#   fixed_adjust              acc_and_pay = accrue on adjusted dates (default)
#                             pay         = accrue on UNADJUSTED dates; adjust pay date only
#                             none        = adjust nothing
#   fixed_roll_convention     forward / forward_eom (from effective; stub at back)
#                             backward / backward_eom (from maturity; stub at front)
#                             *_eom snaps month-end-anchored periods to month-end; blank => forward_eom
#   fixed_payment_delay_bdays int >=0 business-day lag accrual end -> cash; blank => 0
#   fixed_principal_exchange  none (default) | start | end | both
#                               start = -notional at start_date; end = +notional at final pay
#   fixed_calculation_calendar   NY_FED (only one registered); blank => NY_FED
#   fixed_payment_calendar       NY_FED; blank => fixed_calculation_calendar (BBG-derived)
#
#   --- Floating leg conventions (optional) ---
#   floating_frequency        1Y/6M/3M/1M/1W/1D; blank => fixed_frequency (standard OIS)
#   floating_daycount         same options as fixed_daycount; blank => ACT/360
#   floating_spread           decimal e.g. 0.0025 = 25 bp; excluded from compounding; blank => 0
#   floating_bus_day_adj      "Bus Day Adj" for floating; <roll>; blank => ModifiedFollowing
#   floating_eff_date_adj     "Eff Date Adj"; <roll>; blank => floating_bus_day_adj
#   floating_pay_date_adj     "Pay Date Adj" (BBG-derived); <roll>; blank => floating_bus_day_adj
#   floating_rst_bus_day_adj  "Rst Bus Day Adj": roll for the (lag-shifted) fixing date;
#                               <roll>; blank => floating_bus_day_adj
#   floating_adjust           acc_and_pay (default) | pay | none (same meaning as fixed_adjust)
#   floating_roll_convention  forward / forward_eom / backward / backward_eom; blank => forward_eom
#   floating_payment_delay_bdays int >=0; blank => 0
#   floating_reset_lag_bdays  int >=0 business-day lookback; 0 = in-arrears OIS (BBG-derived)
#   floating_lockout_bdays    int >=0 frozen fixings at period end; blank => 0
#   floating_principal_exchange  none (default) | start | end | both
#   floating_calculation_calendar  NY_FED; blank => NY_FED
#   floating_fixing_calendar       NY_FED | the reset/fixing calendar; blank => NY_FED
#   floating_payment_calendar      NY_FED; blank => floating_calculation_calendar (BBG-derived)
#
#   description               free text (optional)
#
#   --- Optional holiday-extras columns (add by name only if needed) ---
#   fixed/floating calculation or payment calendar_extras and
#   floating_fixing_calendar_extras : semicolon- or comma-separated ISO dates of extra closures
#   ..._extras_file : path to a CSV/TXT/XLSX list of extra closure dates
#
#   <roll> = None / NoAdjust / Following / ModifiedFollowing / Preceding /
#            ModifiedPreceding / Nearest
#
# BLOOMBERG PARITY: leave *_pay_date_adj / *_payment_calendar /
#   floating_rst_bus_day_adj / floating_reset_lag_bdays blank and the row
#   reproduces a Bloomberg ticket exactly (Bloomberg derives them the same way).
#
# VALIDATION: invalid roll_convention or adjust; maturity<=start; an
#   unregistered calendar; or an unsupported reset/payment type => HARD ERROR
#   (row rejected). adjust=acc_and_pay with an EOM roll or a 30/360 day-count
#   => WARNING only (still prices; logged to manifest.warnings).
#
# === SECTION 2: PRODUCTION-OUTPUT REFERENCE FIELDS ===
#
# These columns feed the prod CSV (IRS Valuation<val_date>-00001.csv) that is
# written by default by every run. They are NOT used by pricing; an empty
# cell writes a blank cell in the output. They sit to the RIGHT of the
# pricing columns; the existing 34 columns above are unchanged.
#
# OVERLAP NOTE: maturity_date and notional are already in Section 1 and feed
# the output columns "Maturity Date" / "Notional 1 Amount" / "Notional 1
# Amount USD" (both notional columns carry the same value since the book is
# USD-only). No duplicate field is needed.
#
#   --- Trade-reference fields (sourced 1:1 from this row) ---
#   quantum_deal_number          Quantum Unique Trade ID
#   oracle_entity_code           Oracle Entity Code (4-digit, e.g. 1000) --
#                                  must match an Entity_Code in the Entity
#                                  Reference Report. ALSO used to build the
#                                  Balance Sheet CCID and PL/OCI CCID (cols
#                                  AU/AV) by looking up the Default RC from
#                                  entity/Entity_Reference_Report.csv. If this
#                                  field is blank or the entity is not in the
#                                  lookup table, both CCID cells are emitted
#                                  blank (no half-built id is ever written).
#   notional_currency            Notional currency of the trade (e.g. USD)
#   intercompany                 true/false -> rendered as Yes/No in the output
#                                  (same boolean parsing as pay_fixed)
#   counterparty_name_quantum    Counterparty Name as per Quantum
#   current_counterparty         Legal Name of the Counterparty.
#                                  IMPORTANT: must be the EXACT string
#                                    "CME Clearing House"
#                                  (case- and whitespace-sensitive) for the
#                                  trade to be flagged as CME-cleared. Anything
#                                  else (including "CME" or "cme clearing
#                                  house") routes to the Bank / OTC-Bilateral
#                                  branch in the output.
#   entity_name_quantum          Amex Entity Abbreviation with Oracle Entity Code
#   reporting_party              Legal Name of the Amex Entity
#   counterparty_location        Country / domicile of counterparty (US / UK / ...)
#   deal_date                    Trade date (ISO) -- when the swap was struck.
#                                  Distinct from start_date (effective date);
#                                  the two typically differ by ~2 business days.
#   netting_id                   Unique netting-database key (free text)
#   cash_flow_netting_allowed    Multiple-payments netting indicator (Yes/No)
#   position_netting_allowed     MTM position netting indicator (Yes/No)
#
# Output fields that are NOT sourced from this template (the prod writer fills
# them itself):
#   * As of Date  <- val_date passed on the CLI
#   * Clean / Accrued / NPV / DV01 / Hedged Debt MTM  <- pricer output
#   * Valuation Currency = "USD"; Product = "IR"; HCL Type = "Interest Rate Swap"
#   * Collateral Level = "Fully Collateralized"
#   * Sub-Product2, Counterparty Type, QCCP / Cleared / Cash-Settled CCP
#     indicators  <- branched off current_counterparty == "CME Clearing House"
#   * DA / DL / Asset Liability Tag  <- branched off the sign of NPV
#   * Fields marked "Not Required" in the spec (Trade Reference Number,
#     Internal Reference Number, Period Start/End/Payment dates, Pay Rec
#     Status, Component Type, Coupon FV, Intrinsic Value FV, Time Value FV,
#     InternalFacing-StreetFacing, Counterparty Code) are always written blank.
#   * Balance Sheet CCID (AU) and PL/OCI CCID (AV) are NOT input fields --
#     they are composed from oracle_entity_code + the Entity Reference Report
#     lookup + the NPV-sign-driven natural account (Asset=192001 /
#     Liability=392001 / PL=465012). See plan.md "CCID composition".
#
# Lines starting with # are ignored. Blank rows are ignored.
trade_id,notional,pay_fixed,fixed_rate,start_date,maturity_date,fixed_frequency,fixed_daycount,fixed_bus_day_adj,fixed_eff_date_adj,fixed_pay_date_adj,fixed_adjust,fixed_roll_convention,fixed_payment_delay_bdays,fixed_principal_exchange,fixed_calculation_calendar,fixed_payment_calendar,floating_frequency,floating_daycount,floating_spread,floating_bus_day_adj,floating_eff_date_adj,floating_pay_date_adj,floating_rst_bus_day_adj,floating_adjust,floating_roll_convention,floating_payment_delay_bdays,floating_reset_lag_bdays,floating_lockout_bdays,floating_principal_exchange,floating_calculation_calendar,floating_fixing_calendar,floating_payment_calendar,description,quantum_deal_number,oracle_entity_code,notional_currency,intercompany,counterparty_name_quantum,current_counterparty,entity_name_quantum,reporting_party,counterparty_location,deal_date,netting_id,cash_flow_netting_allowed,position_netting_allowed
